<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFA4672DFF4E0EAF5A25501D" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFA4672DFF4E0EAF5A25501D" blockId="19.[140,1108,1398,1672]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA4672DFF4E0EAF596853EF" bold="true" box="[185,312,1433,1459]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA4672DFF4E0EAF596353EF" box="[185,307,1433,1459]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species can be easily distinguished from all congeners, except for 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA4672DFF7B0E88595B538B" authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[140,267,1470,1495]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esyunini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA4672DFF7B0E88595B538B" box="[140,267,1470,1495]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">H. esyunini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F8F47135FFA4672DFEE30E8859045384" box="[276,340,1470,1496]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by a relatively shorter tip of the cymbium, flattened apical part of the tegulum, and undivided tegular apophysis. From the sibling species 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA4672DFC470ED75C7E53A6" authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[944,1070,1505,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esyunini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA4672DFC470ED75C7E53A6" box="[944,1070,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">H. esyunini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F8F47135FFA4672DFBC30ED758F45042" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA4672DFF460D32590F5041" baseAuthorityName="Liang &amp; Wang" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[177,351,1540,1565]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinjiangensis">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA4672DFF460D32590F5041" box="[177,351,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">H. xinjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by its larger size, different shape of the tegular apophysis and median plate of the epigyne.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
