<paragraph id="D10C105CFFA4672AFF4E0D7F5902543B" blockId="19.[140,1108,1398,1672]" lastBlockId="20.[140,1108,167,1143]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA4672DFF4E0D7F5919503F" bold="true" box="[185,329,1609,1635]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
(translated from original description). “Female. Total length 5.8, body flat. Cephalic part of carapace swollen, the position of PME highest. Cervical groove deep. Thorax low and flat. Eye area brown, 8 eyes in 2 rows. Both AER, PER curved, AER curved stronger than PER. ALE white, others 6 eyes black, AME largest, located in the front of head; ALE small, located below in front of PLE. 4 eyes of PER near same size. Chelicera small, yellowish brown, with one promarginal tooth and no retromarginal. Pedipalps and legs yellowish brown, each segments of pedipalps and legs with blackish brown annuli in the median and the distal. Tarsus with 3 claws. Upper claw with a single tooth. Leg formula 2143. Opisthosoma dorsally with yellowish brown scales and grayish brown spots. Heart spot black, with three pairs of muscular depressions. The venter yellow, without marking. Anterior spinnerets robust, their distal segment small. Median spinnerets thin, nearly the same length as anterior ones. Rear spinnerets located on the sides of median ones. The distal segment same length as opisthosoma, smaller than the basal one. Colulus present. Epigyne brown, septum inverse T-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFA3672AFF4E09465BA354D6" blockId="20.[140,1108,167,1143]" box="[185,1011,624,651]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Male. Total length 5.00. Habitus, colour and markings style as in female.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFA3672AFF4E09A55B67548D" blockId="20.[140,1108,167,1143]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">This species inhabits crevices and holes of walls. It is a common species. Its colouration is cryptic and therefore it is not easy to find specimens.”</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFA3672AFF4E09EF5C04559B" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFA3672AFF4E09EF5C04559B" blockId="20.[140,1108,167,1143]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFF4E09EF591454AF" bold="true" box="[185,324,729,755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFF4E09EF596F54AF" box="[185,319,729,755]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" reason="1">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="0E08AEFEFFA3672AFEBB09EC59D354A8" box="[332,387,730,756]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Type</typeStatus>
specimens (2♁, 
<specimenCount id="C7B5DBD5FFA3672AFDB309EC5A3154A8" box="[580,609,730,756]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" type="female">2♀</specimenCount>
) were supposedly deposited in the Department of Plant Protection, 
<collectingRegion id="1377DEBEFFA3672AFE4609CB5A42554B" box="[433,530,765,791]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
August 1 
<superScript id="26C6BD14FFA3672AFD8909CB5AD95557" attach="left" box="[638,649,765,779]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">st</superScript>
Agricultural College, Urumqi, 
<collectingRegion id="1377DEBEFFA3672AFC1C09CB5C1F554B" box="[1003,1103,765,791]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFA3672AFF7B081658825566" box="[140,210,800,826]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFA3672AFF15081659B95566" author="Liang T &amp; Wang JF" box="[226,489,800,827]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" pagination="56 - 58" refId="ref19386" refString="Liang T, Wang JF (1989) A new species of spiders of the genus Hersilia in Xinjiang. Journal of August 1 st Agricultural College 12: 56 - 58 [in Chinese]." type="journal article" year="1989">Liang and Wang 1989</bibRefCitation>
). At our request, Shuqiang Li tried to find these 
<typeStatus id="0E08AEFEFFA3672AFBED08175C045567" box="[1050,1108,801,827]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">types</typeStatus>
but failed. It seems that after the retirement of Tie Liang these specimens were lost or transferred. The embolus base was not depicted by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFA3672AFD2F08515BBF55DD" author="Liang T &amp; Wang JF" box="[728,1007,871,897]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" pagination="56 - 58" refId="ref19386" refString="Liang T, Wang JF (1989) A new species of spiders of the genus Hersilia in Xinjiang. Journal of August 1 st Agricultural College 12: 56 - 58 [in Chinese]." type="journal article" year="1989">Liang and Wang (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. Judging from the conformation of the epigyne in its sibling, 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA3672AFD2A08BD5B0C55F8" authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[733,860,907,932]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esyunini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFD2A08BD5B0C55F8" box="[733,860,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">H. esyunini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F8F47135FFA3672AFC9308BC5BF355F8" box="[868,931,906,932]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, it is likely that median plate of the epigyne and vulva (endogyne) have been somewhat misinterpreted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFA3672AFF4E08E659F4522B" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFA3672AFF4E08E659F4522B" blockId="20.[140,1108,167,1143]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFF4E08E6590855B6" bold="true" box="[185,344,976,1002]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFF4E08E6590355B6" box="[185,339,976,1002]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA3672AFE9708E75A4055B6" baseAuthorityName="Liang &amp; Wang" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[352,528,977,1002]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinjiangensis">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFE9708E75A4055B6" box="[352,528,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">H. xinjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from central 
<collectingRegion id="1377DEBEFFA3672AFCA108E65BE755B6" box="[854,951,976,1002]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFA3672AFC3F08E65C4455B7" box="[968,1044,976,1003]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">China</collectingCountry>
). It is the northernmost species of the genus and of the entire family 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA3672AFCA008C55B855251" box="[855,981,1011,1037]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hersiliidae</taxonomicName>
. In Europe (Iberian Peninsula), the northernmost locality of 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA3672AFD440F21595D5208" authority="(Lucas, 1846) (Ribera et al. 1988)" authorityName="Ribera et al." authorityYear="1988" baseAuthorityName="Lucas" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Tama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFD440F215B07526D" box="[691,855,1047,1073]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Tama edwardsi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFA3672AFC920F215BA1526E" author="Lucas H" box="[869,1009,1047,1074]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" pagination="89 - 271" refId="ref19423" refString="Lucas H (1846) Histoire naturelle des animaux articules. In: Exploration scientifique de l'Algerie pendant les annees 1840, 1841, 1842 publiee par ordre du Gouvernement et avec le concours d'une commission academique. Paris, Sciences physiques, Zoologie 1: 89 - 271." type="journal article" year="1846">Lucas, 1846</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFA3672AFBF00F2159555208" author="Ribera C &amp; Ferrandez MA &amp; Perez JA" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" pagination="97 - 103" refId="ref19887" refString="Ribera C, Ferrandez MA, Perez JA (1988) Los hersilidos (Araneae, Hersiliidae) de la fauna Iberica. Miscellania Zoologica 10: 97 - 103." type="journal article" year="1988">Ribera et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is in northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFA3672AFE160F0C5A105208" box="[481,576,1082,1108]" name="Portugal" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">Portugal</collectingCountry>
ca. 
<geoCoordinate id="B487769BFFA3672AFD9A0F0C5AFD5208" box="[621,685,1082,1108]" degrees="41" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" precision="55555" value="41.0">41°N</geoCoordinate>
, while the 
<typeStatus id="0E08AEFEFFA3672AFCDF0F0C5B085208" box="[808,856,1082,1108]" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFA3672AFC210F0D5898522B" baseAuthorityName="Liang &amp; Wang" baseAuthorityYear="1989" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinjiangensis">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFA3672AFC210F0D5898522B" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="95">H. xinjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lies north of 
<geoCoordinate id="B487769BFFA3672AFEA80F6B59F0522B" box="[351,416,1117,1143]" degrees="44" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="20" pageNumber="95" precision="55555" value="44.0">44°N</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
